<p>I'm trying to write some data to registry using Delphi. When I test the program it crashes and gives me this error:</p>  <blockquote>   <p>First chance exception at $00607587. Exception class $C0000005 with message 'access violation at 0x00607587: read of address 0x000003cc'. Process guiclient.exe (2364)</p> </blockquote>  <p>... pointing me this line:</p>  <pre><code>reg.WriteString('email', SettingsForm.email_edit.Text); </code></pre>  <p>I tried running it as administrator but still the same. How can I fix this error?</p>  <p><strong>EDIT:</strong> I excluded SettingsForm (which contains these code) from "auto create forms". The variable reg is defined in the block of code I given. I implemented "Registry". <code>email_edit</code> is a TEdit control.</p>  <p>var section:</p>  <pre><code>var   reg        : TRegistry;   openResult : Boolean;  const   ApplicationTitle = 'Gazi Bilgisayar - Chromium'; </code></pre>  <p>Here's that block of my code:</p>  <pre><code>try     reg := TRegistry.Create(KEY_READ);     reg.RootKey := HKEY_CURRENT_USER;      if (not reg.KeyExists('Software\' + ApplicationTitle + '\')) then     begin       MessageDlg('Registry anahtarı bulunmadı ve oluşturuluyor.',                   mtInformation, mbOKCancel, 0);     end;     reg.Access := KEY_WRITE;     openResult := reg.OpenKey('Software\' + ApplicationTitle + '\', True);      if not openResult = True then     begin       MessageDlg('Registry anahtarı oluşturulamadı. Programdan çıkılıyor.',                   mtError, mbOKCancel, 0);       Exit();     end;      { Checking if the values exist and inserting when neccesary }      if not reg.KeyExists('email') then     begin       reg.WriteString('email', SettingsForm.email_edit.Text);     end; finally     reg.CloseKey();     reg.Free; end; </code></pre>